{"questionId":"9706","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The intensity level of sound, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span> measured in decibels (dB), is a function of the sound&nbsp;intensity, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"S\">\n  <mi>S</mi>\n</math></span> watts per square metre (W m<sup>−2</sup>). The intensity level is given by the following formula.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L = 10\\,{\\text{lo}}{{\\text{g}}_{10}}\\left( {S \\times {{10}^{12}}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>lo</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>10</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>12</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"S\">\n  <mi>S</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≥ 0.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>A rock concert has an intensity level of 112 dB. Find the sound intensity, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"S\">\n  <mi>S</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"112 = 10\\,{\\text{lo}}{{\\text{g}}_{10}}\\left( {S \\times {{10}^{12}}} \\right)\">\n  <mn>112</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>lo</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>g</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>10</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>S</mi>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>12</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>0.158 (W m<sup>−2</sup>) (0.158489… (W m<sup>−2</sup>))&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9706","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"A rock concert has an intensity level of 112 dB. Find the sound intensity, S .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.5—Intro to logs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}